---
import BaseLayout from '@/components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import DesignWorkflowStrip from '@/components/diagrams/DesignWorkflowStrip.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Design Workflow — Claude Design, Figma, Cursor"
  description="How Moe Qadan designs in context. Claude Design as part of a current front-end design loop, alongside Figma, Cursor, and WebSim — across ChatOBD2, MagTek, the Sawa marketing site, and advisor platforms."
  keywords={[
    'Moe Qadan',
    'design workflow',
    'Claude Design',
    'Figma',
    'Cursor',
    'design engineering',
    'design systems',
    'product design process',
    'AI-assisted design',
  ]}
>
  <div class="design">
    <div class="design__hero">
      <div class="container-site">
        <span class="design__eyebrow">Design workflow</span>
        <h1 class="design__title">
          Claude Design <em>(visual branch)</em>.
        </h1>
        <p class="design__subtitle">
          Claude Design is one branch of the execution layer. I use
          it when structure alone isn't enough and the problem needs
          to be seen.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container-site design__body">
      <div class="design__strip" data-reveal>
        <span class="design__strip-caption">The visual branch of the execution layer</span>
        <DesignWorkflowStrip />
      </div>

      <p class="design__manifesto" data-reveal>
        I don't think of design and build as separate stages. Most of
        my work happens in code, against the components and tokens
        the product is built from.
      </p>

      <div class="design__prose">
        <p class="design__para" data-reveal>
          That usually means:
        </p>
        <ul class="design__bullets" data-reveal>
          <li>new flows</li>
          <li>layout and hierarchy decisions</li>
          <li>comparing multiple directions quickly</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="design__para" data-reveal>
          It's not part of every loop. It earns its place when visual
          reasoning moves the work forward faster than code. Once
          direction is clear, everything resolves back into the same
          system and build loop.
        </p>

        <hr class="design__rule" />

        <h2 class="design__h2">In practice</h2>

        <div class="design__blurbs" data-reveal>
          <figure class="design__blurb">
            <figcaption class="design__blurb-label">When the branch is selected</figcaption>
            <blockquote class="design__blurb-text">
              When a screen is easier to reason about visually than in
              code, the execution layer routes to Claude Design. The
              output is a clearer prompt for the codebase — not a
              handoff to a separate tool.
            </blockquote>
          </figure>
          <figure class="design__blurb">
            <figcaption class="design__blurb-label">Against the system</figcaption>
            <blockquote class="design__blurb-text">
              Claude Design gets more useful when it can work against real
              components, spacing, and styling patterns. That keeps the
              visual exploration grounded in what the product can
              actually carry.
            </blockquote>
          </figure>
        </div>

        <p class="design__note" data-reveal>
          Still a research preview, so the rough edges are real. The
          trade-off is worth it for the speed of getting to something
          tangible.
        </p>

        <hr class="design__rule" />

        <p class="design__para design__para--final" data-reveal>
          The execution layer is branched, not chained. Claude and
          Cursor are interchangeable code environments — both handle
          reasoning, generation, and code; the choice is contextual,
          not by role. Claude Design is the visual branch, conditional
          on the work. Figma stays in the mix for precision and system
          maintenance, WebSim for fast browser experiments. The
          codebase is the source of truth across all of them.
        </p>

        <hr class="design__rule" />

        <h2 class="design__h2">Across the work</h2>

        <p class="design__para" data-reveal>
          Different products, different surfaces, different execution
          environments. Claude Design is the latest branch in a longer
          practice, not the default one.
        </p>

        <section class="design__work" data-reveal>
          <header class="design__work-head">
            <span class="design__work-eyebrow">ChatOBD2</span>
            <h3 class="design__work-title">Both branches of the execution layer.</h3>
          </header>
          <p class="design__work-sub">
            ChatOBD2 is where the loop lives in practice. The product
            surfaces, marketing site, and developer portal route through
            both branches: Claude Design when exploration is visual, the
            code branch (Claude or Cursor — interchangeable) when it isn't. The
            component and token system stays the source of truth, so
            either branch lands in the same codebase.
          </p>
          <div class="design__work-shots">
            <figure class="design__work-shot">
              <img
                src="/images/chatobd2/hero.webp"
                alt="ChatOBD2 marketing hero with phone mockup of a live diagnostic chat."
                width="1440"
                height="900"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption>Marketing hero: same product premise, public-facing format.</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="design__work-shot">
              <img
                src="/images/chatobd2/longitudinal-intelligence.webp"
                alt="ChatOBD2 longitudinal intelligence dashboard with vehicle health score and trend chart."
                width="1440"
                height="900"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption>Trend dashboard: dense data laid out so it reads at a glance.</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="design__work" data-reveal>
          <header class="design__work-head">
            <span class="design__work-eyebrow">MagTek Platform</span>
            <h3 class="design__work-title">Hand-authored CSS on a Bootstrap substrate.</h3>
          </header>
          <p class="design__work-sub">
            MagTek runs on a long-lived ASP.NET MVC platform. Most of
            the design lives in hand-authored CSS over Bootstrap, with
            structure pulled into a Razor component library so a single
            change can land across many pages at once. Adobe XD covered
            the static comp phase; WebSim and Cursor came in for
            browser-first experiments and design-in-code on the
            layouts that were easier to think through in markup than
            in static frames.
          </p>
          <div class="design__work-shots">
            <figure class="design__work-shot">
              <img
                src="/images/magtek/homepage.webp"
                alt="MagTek homepage with metric story and team photography."
                width="1440"
                height="900"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption>Homepage: brand identity built in CSS over a Bootstrap grid.</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="design__work-shot">
              <img
                src="/images/magtek/hardware-card-readers.webp"
                alt="MagTek card readers product page with photography and CTAs."
                width="1440"
                height="900"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption>Hardware page pattern: one template, many product categories.</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="design__work" data-reveal>
          <header class="design__work-head">
            <span class="design__work-eyebrow">Sawa marketing site</span>
            <h3 class="design__work-title">Code branch by default, visual branch when it earned a seat.</h3>
          </header>
          <p class="design__work-sub">
            Sawa's marketing surface ran on the code branch: Cursor as
            the execution environment, Tailwind as the styling system.
            The visual branch was selected only for the sections where
            it was easier to think through visually — live matches, city
            food guides, the swipe-and-match story — and the output
            landed back in Tailwind. The codebase stayed the source of
            truth across both.
          </p>
          <div class="design__work-shots">
            <figure class="design__work-shot">
              <img
                src="/images/sawa/hero.webp"
                alt="Sawa marketing hero — 'idk, you pick' with phone mockup of a matched restaurant card."
                width="1440"
                height="900"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption>Hero: brand and product in one shot.</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="design__work-shot">
              <img
                src="/images/sawa/live-matches.webp"
                alt="Sawa marketing — Matches Happening Now grid of live group dining matches."
                width="1440"
                height="900"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption>Live matches feed: content as proof.</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="design__work" data-reveal>
          <header class="design__work-head">
            <span class="design__work-eyebrow">Advisor Platforms</span>
            <h3 class="design__work-title">CSS implementation against Figma handoffs.</h3>
          </header>
          <p class="design__work-sub">
            At InvestCloud the design teams owned the Figma files. The
            work was translating those files into the proprietary CMS
            and component framework, adapted per institution. Most of
            it was hand-written CSS, mapped to densely structured
            layouts that had to behave across complex data, multiple
            tenants, and per-client branding. Strong handoff hygiene
            matters more than people credit.
          </p>
          <div class="design__work-shots">
            <figure class="design__work-shot">
              <img
                src="/images/financial-platforms/chase.webp"
                alt="Chase homepage built on the InvestCloud framework."
                width="1440"
                height="900"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption>Chase: dense, conservative, login-forward.</figcaption>
            </figure>
            <figure class="design__work-shot">
              <img
                src="/images/financial-platforms/cetera.webp"
                alt="Cetera homepage built on the InvestCloud framework."
                width="1440"
                height="900"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption>Cetera: a different brand, the same underlying framework.</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .design__hero {
    padding-top: calc(60px + var(--space-10));
    padding-bottom: var(--space-10);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .design__hero {
      padding-top: calc(64px + var(--space-16));
      padding-bottom: var(--space-12);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    }
  }

  .design__eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .design__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(38px, 9vw, 80px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 18ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .design__title em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .design__subtitle {
    font-size: clamp(17px, 1.8vw, 20px);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .design__body {
    padding-bottom: var(--space-16);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-10);
    max-width: 1080px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .design__body {
      padding-bottom: var(--space-24);
      gap: var(--space-12);
    }
  }

  .design__strip {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-8);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
  }

  .design__strip-caption {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
  }

  .design__manifesto {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.4vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 38ch;
    padding-block: var(--space-2);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
  }

  .design__prose {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .design__bullets {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .design__bullets li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 24px;
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.5vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .design__bullets li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.7em;
    width: 12px;
    height: 1px;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .design__para {
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.5vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .design__para--final {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-size: clamp(16px, 1.6vw, 18px);
  }

  .design__rule {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin: var(--space-4) 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .design__h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.5vw, 30px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .design__blurbs {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .design__blurbs {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-5);
    }
  }

  .design__blurb {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    padding: var(--space-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .design__blurb-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
  }

  .design__blurb-text {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(16px, 1.7vw, 19px);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
  }

  .design__note {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    max-width: 60ch;
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0;
  }

  .design__work {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding-top: var(--space-6);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
  }

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .design__work {
      gap: var(--space-5);
      padding-top: var(--space-8);
    }
  }

  .design__work:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  .design__work-head {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .design__work-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
  }

  .design__work-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.6vw, 30px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 28ch;
  }

  .design__work-sub {
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.5vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .design__work-shots {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .design__work-shots {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-5);
    }
  }

  .design__work-shot {
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .design__work-shot img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  }

  .design__work-shot figcaption {
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
  }
</style>
